{"updated_at":"2011-10-11T19:57:22Z","description":"Digital Segment Display - 140byt.es","public":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/gists/1272408","created_at":"2011-10-08T15:11:20Z","comments":8,"html_url":"https://gist.github.com/1272408","git_pull_url":"git://gist.github.com/1272408.git","forks":[],"git_push_url":"git@gist.github.com:1272408.git","user":{"login":"aemkei","url":"https://api.github.com/users/aemkei","gravatar_id":"0d9da77bb99bea710cbf711ed08e57d7","avatar_url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0d9da77bb99bea710cbf711ed08e57d7?d=https://a248.e.akamai.net/assets.github.com%2Fimages%2Fgravatars%2Fgravatar-140.png","id":1521},"files":{"annotated.js":{"content":"function(\n  a,                     // number to convert\n  b,                     // output placeholder\n  c                      // data placeholder\n){                       \n\n  for (                  // parse binary data\n    \n    a in                 \n      c = \"ĨǮŉŌƎĜĘŮĈČ\"   // data is stored in unicode character\n      .charCodeAt(a)     // convert character to integer\n      .toString(2)       // convert to binary representaion\n  )                      \n                         \n  b = [b] + \n  \n    \" |_\"[               // draw space, \"|\" or \"_\" based on position\n      1 ^                \n      c[a] &&            // check binary state\n      a%2 + 1            // shift mapping index\n    ] + [\n      \"\\n\"[\n        ~-a%4            // add line break after char 1 and 5\n      ]\n    ]\n    \n  return b               // return the output string\n}","size":858,"filename":"annotated.js","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1272408/759b81d75d722bf82cc2fb157204e69658d805f2/annotated.js"},"example.html":{"content":"<!DOCTYPE html> \n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html;charset=UTF-8\">\n<title>Digital Clock - 140bytes</title>\n<style type=\"text/css\">\n  body { font-weight: bold; color: lime; background: black; }\n  pre { display: inline-block; width: auto; }\n</style>\n<div id=\"time\"></div>\n\n<script>\nvar digits =   \nfunction(a,b,c){for(a in c=\"ĨǮŉŌƎĜĘŮĈČ\".charCodeAt(a).toString(2))b=[b]+\" |_\"[1^c[a]&&a%2+1]+[\"\\n\"[~-a%4]];return b}\n\nfunction pad(number){\n  return (number < 10 ? \"0\" : \"\") + number; \n}\n\nsetInterval(function(){\n  \n  var display = \"\",\n    date = new Date(),\n    time = pad(date.getHours()) +\n      pad(date.getMinutes()) + \n      pad(date.getSeconds()),\n    i;\n\n  for(i in time){\n    display += \"<pre>\" + digits(time[i]) + \"</pre>\";\n    if (i==1 || i==3){\n      display += \"<pre>\\n.\\n.</pre>\"\n    }\n  }\n  \n  document.getElementById( \"time\" ).innerHTML = display\n  \n  \n}, 1000);\n\n</script>","size":911,"filename":"example.html","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1272408/1a3357eaae0be62987247f70bf65a752a28fa4b4/example.html"},"LICENSE.txt":{"content":"            DO WHAT THE FUCK YOU WANT TO PUBLIC LICENSE\n                    Version 2, December 2004\n\n Copyright (C) 2011 YOUR_NAME_HERE <YOUR_URL_HERE>\n\n Everyone is permitted to copy and distribute verbatim or modified\n copies of this license document, and changing it is allowed as long\n as the name is changed.\n\n            DO WHAT THE FUCK YOU WANT TO PUBLIC LICENSE\n   TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR COPYING, DISTRIBUTION AND MODIFICATION\n\n  0. You just DO WHAT THE FUCK YOU WANT TO.","size":483,"filename":"LICENSE.txt","raw_url":"https://gist.github.com/raw/1272408/dfb480a5038214d152544bddb412dfe2e8656413/LICENSE.txt"},"README.md":{"content":"Digital Segment Display - 140byt.es\n===================================\n\nConverts single digits into old-school ASCII string. \n\nSee my [old-school digital clock](http://jsfiddle.net/aemkei/u9vRw/embedded/result/) example.\n\n\n### Digit List\n\n     _      _  _       _   _  _   _   _\n    | |  |  _| _| |_| |_  |_   | |_| |_|\n    |_|  | |_  _|   |  _| |_|  | |_|  _|\n\n### Sample Clock ###\n\n             _  _     _  _  \n    | |_| .  _| _| . |_   | \n